The old Potchefstroom train station in the North West, where hundreds of photoshoots were held, has caught fire. Police spokesperson Col Adele Myburgh confirmed that a fire broke out at the train station on Saturday. “There is still smoke coming from the station.” Myburgh said that once the scene has been declared safe, a team of specialists would be sent to determine the cause of the blaze. An inquest case is under investigation. TimesLIVE